Dialogue: 5,0:04:24.37,0:04:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it Tsumugu?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:25.62,0:04:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:27.13,0:04:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't changed at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:29.69,0:04:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When it comes to the person you like,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:32.02,0:04:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not quite yourself.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:35.47,0:04:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:36.81,0:04:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you can tell me what's on your mind.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:39.25,0:04:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If it might help you feel better, I mean.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:43.87,0:04:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about my feelings.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:46.11,0:04:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaname...
Dialogue: 5,0:04:47.44,0:04:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how hard I tried not to be,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:49.28,0:04:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was always the odd man out.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:51.87,0:04:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, I knew that if things didn't work out with {you and }Hikari,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:54.79,0:04:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it was going to be Tsumugu next, and not me.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:57.90,0:05:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I don't love him!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:00.65,0:05:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not allowed to love Tsumugu...
Dialogue: 5,0:05:04.40,0:05:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:06.25,0:05:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If I fell in love with anyone other than Hikari,
Dialogue: 5,0:05:09.39,0:05:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd be like betraying everyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:11.48,0:05:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd be betraying everyone whose time stopped five years ago!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:15.62,0:05:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 5,0:05:16.76,0:05:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I love Hikari!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:19.43,0:05:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't just forget that!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:21.95,0:05:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I made sure I never forgot.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:24.65,0:05:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When Hikari woke up, I was so scared.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:28.21,0:05:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew I was the only one \Nwho grew up and changed,
Dialogue: 5,0:05:30.73,0:05:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,but it wasn't just that.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:32.68,0:05:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I was scared he'd see through \Nme about everything.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:36.67,0:05:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, he said I hadn't changed at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:40.71,0:05:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That made me so happy.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:42.95,0:05:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt so sure my feelings \Nfor him hadn't changed!{i felt i still loved him or i thought i still loved him.}
Dialogue: 5,0:05:46.11,0:05:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sure I still loved him!{i felt/thought that (my love had endured)}
Dialogue: 5,0:05:49.31,0:05:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 5,0:05:52.11,0:05:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,None of that matters anymore.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:55.77,0:05:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all here now.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:58.43,0:05:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We came back.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:00.95,0:06:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to hide or deny your feelings anymore.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:07.39,0:06:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But Manaka loves Tsumugu.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:10.47,0:06:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to try to get back \NManaka's ability to love,
Dialogue: 5,0:06:14.35,0:06:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,so I can't just accept his feelings for me.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:17.83,0:06:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Manaka has nothing to do with{ this}—
Dialogue: 5,0:06:19.02,0:06:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, she does!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:22.02,0:06:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Your stubbornness \Nhasn't changed a bit either.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:35.75,0:06:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep hearing the sea...
Dialogue: 5,0:06:41.41,0:06:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You done, Manaka-chan?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:43.16,0:06:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I open the door?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:44.56,0:06:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, of course!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:47.49,0:06:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So in kindergarten today, \NAkira wrote a letter.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:51.79,0:06:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you mind reading it?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:53.74,0:06:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A letter?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:55.29,0:06:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is it for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.39,0:06:59.31,Akira dakara,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.8\c&H869279&\fax0.35\fscx158\fscy115\fsp1\frz340.6\pos(723,154)}I love Manaka
Dialogue: 5,0:06:58.71,0:07:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"I love... Manaka"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.31,0:06:59.44,Akira dakara,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.8\c&H869279&\fax0.35\fscx155.7\fscy113.32\fsp1\frz339.36\pos(701.54,189.18)}I love Manaka
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.44,0:06:59.56,Akira dakara,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.8\c&H869279&\fax0.35\fscx153.38\fscy111.64\fsp1\frz338.11\pos(678.16,230.32)}I love Manaka
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.56,0:06:59.69,Akira dakara,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.8\c&H869279&\fax0.35\fscx151.14\fscy110.01\fsp1\frz338.85\pos(601.05,291.78)}I love Manaka
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:06:59.77,Akira dakara,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.8\c&H869279&\fax0.35\fscx151.21\fscy110.06\fsp1\frz339.59\pos(525.29,353.59)}I love Manaka
Dialogue: 5,0:07:05.75,0:07:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As his mom, I can't say I don't have mixed feelings about it,
Dialogue: 5,0:07:08.58,0:07:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but it makes me sort of happy too.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:10.91,0:07:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you think?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:13.70,0:07:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Akira! \NNo need to get all bashful...
Dialogue: 5,0:07:15.70,0:07:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,right, Manaka-chan?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:18.17,0:07:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:19.35,0:07:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Manaka-chan?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:21.07,0:07:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot...
Dialogue: 5,0:07:22.04,0:07:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Rejected already.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:26.59,0:07:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let it get to you, Akira!
Dialogue: 5,0:07:29.00,0:07:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:30.44,0:07:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't you know your name means, "Don't give up"?{lolol}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.64,0:07:43.15,Akira dakara,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.8\c&H7D5936&\fax0.55\fsp1\fscx230\fscy168\pos(472.29,166.59)\frz0.07}I love {\frz4.5}Manaka
Dialogue: 5,0:07:43.63,0:07:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:49.05,0:07:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:51.77,0:07:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Be quiet.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:53.89,0:07:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 5,0:07:56.33,0:07:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Be quiet!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:03.21,0:08:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even though it hurts, Hikari's doing all he can to get Manaka-san's feelings back.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:10.01,0:08:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The least I can do is...
Dialogue: 5,0:08:12.71,0:08:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Miuna?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:16.05,0:08:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:19.39,0:08:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,About Manaka's pendant...
Dialogue: 5,0:08:21.47,0:08:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to admit it,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:23.55,0:08:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but I've got plenty to thank you for.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:26.27,0:08:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you "hate to admit it"?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:28.67,0:08:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just...
Dialogue: 5,0:08:30.95,0:08:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You made that flag,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:32.56,0:08:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and you helped us get to Shioshishio too.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:36.05,0:08:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess I can't treat you like a little kid anymore.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:39.08,0:08:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to put this,
Dialogue: 5,0:08:41.39,0:08:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but it feels like I'll never be able to pay you back for all this.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:44.77,0:08:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, aren't you being honest!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:46.45,0:08:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:47.80,0:08:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like you, that's all.{technical comma splice}
Dialogue: 5,0:08:49.47,0:08:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess if it's for Manaka-san, you can even change your personality.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:52.59,0:08:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Why'd you have to put it like that?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:56.36,0:09:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Since Hikari has feelings for Manaka-san,\N the least I can do for him{ is}...
Dialogue: 5,0:09:06.73,0:09:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to bed.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:08.36,0:09:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay...
Dialogue: 5,0:09:09.96,0:09:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:11.09,0:09:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...is make sure he doesn't find out about my feelings for him.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:19.43,0:09:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Hii-kun.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:20.66,0:09:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:21.40,0:09:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Morning.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:22.56,0:09:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:23.74,0:09:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I packed it full for you.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:24.70,0:09:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:25.98,0:09:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where's Miuna?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:27.81,0:09:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She said she was going to school early.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:30.75,0:09:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are Akari and Akira?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:32.38,0:09:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Akari took Akira to kindergarten early, too.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:34.82,0:09:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:42.25,0:09:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't hear it this morning.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:44.83,0:09:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:46.31,0:09:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you in love with anybody, Hii-kun?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:49.55,0:09:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Where'd {\i1}that{\i0} question come from?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:53.23,0:09:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just... I don't quite understand it.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:56.14,0:09:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I know what "love" is.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:59.69,0:10:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's strange.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:01.67,0:10:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure I love all of you,{i think i love you all,}
Dialogue: 5,0:10:04.54,0:10:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but I somehow get this feeling that there's more to it.{but i get the feeling thats not really all there is to it}{-> only platonic love remains, not romantic}
Dialogue: 5,0:10:09.77,0:10:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How could this...{i think hes asking himself/a supernatural entity why manaka has to endure so much when she did nothing to deserve it}
Dialogue: 5,0:10:11.35,0:10:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:12.69,0:10:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, it's just like {\i1}that{\i0}!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:14.86,0:10:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"That"?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:15.70,0:10:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, exactly.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:17.28,0:10:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, no need to worry about it.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:19.34,0:10:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All this stuff is gonna work out somehow.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:21.21,0:10:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What stuff?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:22.56,0:10:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, stuff!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:24.56,0:10:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:26.10,0:10:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what I said!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:33.17,0:10:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like you're feeling well today.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:35.29,0:10:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:36.98,0:10:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So I was thinking...
Dialogue: 5,0:10:38.33,0:10:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it be okay if I started living in a dorm next year?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:41.44,0:10:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked my instructor about it,
Dialogue: 5,0:10:43.27,0:10:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and he said there's a dorm room open.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:45.69,0:10:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I can pay for it with my part-time job...
Dialogue: 5,0:10:48.13,0:10:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So—
Dialogue: 5,0:10:49.08,0:10:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:52.28,0:10:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:55.33,0:10:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandpa,
Dialogue: 5,0:10:57.10,0:11:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the other day, you never finished the story about the Wooden Maiden.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:00.01,0:11:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You said the sea god took something precious from the maiden before he sent her back,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:04.46,0:11:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but what happened after she returned to the surface?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:08.59,0:11:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The man she loved was dead.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:10.77,0:11:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:12.41,0:11:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He went searching for her at sea, and he drowned.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:16.64,0:11:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What happened then?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:18.49,0:11:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no one waiting for the maiden when she returned to the surface.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:23.91,0:11:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:28.99,0:11:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tsumugu.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:30.33,0:11:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys going home?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:31.16,0:11:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:33.31,0:11:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you make that?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:35.18,0:11:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:36.31,0:11:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it that obvious \Nthat it's handmade?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:37.94,0:11:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:39.50,0:11:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's really pretty.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:41.24,0:11:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the red-bellied \Nsea slug is really happy!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:43.39,0:11:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A red-bellied sea slug?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:45.83,0:11:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the slug that responds when you tell it your feelings, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:49.05,0:11:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You really {\i1}do{\i0} know \Neverything about the sea, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:52.55,0:11:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hikari, Kaname.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:54.36,0:11:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a minute?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:55.91,0:11:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna talk to you guys, man-to-man.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:59.05,0:12:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"Man-to-man"?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:03.03,0:12:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please curse me once more?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:05.49,0:12:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:06.68,0:12:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes all the fun out of it when \Nsomeone {\i1}asks{\i0} for a curse, you know.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:11.40,0:12:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I can imagine.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:12.50,0:12:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:13.70,0:12:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanted us to come with you just so you could ask {\i1}that{\i0}?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:16.48,0:12:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The Boatdrift Ceremony.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:17.44,0:12:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:18.21,0:12:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If we offer another Wooden Maiden,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:20.83,0:12:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we may be able to delay the end for the surface,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:24.55,0:12:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and Mukaido might get her feelings back.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:28.06,0:12:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, now just a sec.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:29.86,0:12:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What do the Boatdrift Ceremony and Manaka{ have to do with}—
Dialogue: 5,0:12:31.70,0:12:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Detritus.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:33.17,0:12:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the dead cells of plankton and other microorganisms that are afloat in the sea.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:39.03,0:12:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When I got my Ena, I felt something.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:41.77,0:12:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the multitude of emotions that are afloat in the sea just like detritus.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:46.55,0:12:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A multitude of emotions?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:48.18,0:12:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean, like what we heard the other day about the sea god's dissolved emotions?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:54.51,0:12:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just the sea god's.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:56.57,0:13:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}I don't know if it was the memories of the people \Nfrom Shishio, or if it was from the fish around me.{2.5+3.4}
Dialogue: 5,0:13:03.47,0:13:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But among all those nameless, timeless feelings,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:07.04,0:13:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I sensed a presence I knew very well.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:10.35,0:13:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure those were Mukaido's feelings.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:13.60,0:13:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:15.10,0:13:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You said that when Mukaido \Nbecame the sacrifice,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:17.78,0:13:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the sea god's spirit fire and the \Nfragments of emotions became one,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:21.38,0:13:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and an equilibrium was reached.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:23.37,0:13:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we offer another sacrifice—
Dialogue: 5,0:13:25.68,0:13:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a sec! You're not suggesting we make Manaka the sacrifice again—
Dialogue: 5,0:13:28.34,0:13:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That pendant.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:30.13,0:13:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If it truly holds Mukaido's feelings
Dialogue: 5,0:13:33.19,0:13:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and we put it on a Wooden Maiden,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:35.10,0:13:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't that serve as a \Nreplacement for Mukaido?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:37.75,0:13:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If the sea god's emotions are led to believe that Mukaido has returned to the sea,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:42.60,0:13:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they may return her feelings back to her.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:45.59,0:13:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, are you even listening to yourself?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:49.02,0:13:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You sound crazy!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:50.43,0:13:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to at least try.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:53.22,0:13:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you help us?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:56.23,0:13:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:57.60,0:14:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we get a whole bunch of people involved and it winds up being all for nothing again?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:01.90,0:14:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That may happen, but doing nothing won't solve anything.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:04.36,0:14:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:07.73,0:14:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You said something very similar \Nfive years ago, Hikari, did you not?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:13.15,0:14:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:14.37,0:14:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems amusing. I shall lend a hand.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:16.36,0:14:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{replace}Uroko-sama{Lord Uroko}!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:17.92,0:14:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,However, a Boatdrift Ceremony done only by those from the surface is but a sham.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:23.06,0:14:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that, do you still want to try?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:24.56,0:14:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:25.38,0:14:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:26.14,0:14:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better than doing nothing at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:29.05,0:14:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
